The Eskom office in Empangeni on the KwaZulu-Natal north coast was disconnected for non-payment of its “high” electricity bill on Thursday. The power utility owes  the uMhlathuze municipality almost R500,000. The city said it was conducting electricity disconnections on entities owing the municipality large sums and  with “high electricity debt”. “The city is  disconnecting Mhlathuze Water in Richards Bay  and will  disconnect Eskom at Empangeni, and the departments of education, transport and social welfare,” municipal spokesperson Bongani Gina said  before the operation on Thursday. Eskom didn't immediately respond. TimesLIVE Support independent journalism by subscribing to the Sunday Times. Just R20 for the first month.